snippet.textDisplay: Beautiful video! I just would like to give a bit of advice. Soy and tofu are very bad for cats. They have been linked to many intolerances and skin issues. Also the plant protein is not well assimilated by carnivores so really nothing good coming out of it. Also, you could really improve the nutrition of this dish by adding 5% liver and 5% secreting organs such as brain or kidney. I also don't see any source of calcium. A pinch of eggshell or calcium carbonate would be necessarity. And maybe feeding more muscle meat than all this fish, this meal is also not high in taurine and vitamin A.
